They are intersex, with intersex being part of the group of about 60 diseases diagnosed as disorders of sex development, an umbrella term for people with atypical chromosomes or gonads (ovaries or testicles) or abnormally developed sex organs.
Wallis Simpson could have been intersex.
Gender identification is still not well understood, but most specialists in the United States say that when gender cannot be determined, it is best to use the best information available to assign it, then wait and follow the psychological and physical development of the child before considering surgery, if necessary.
