For Justin Timberlake, if the work is necessary to &quot;be considered good&quot;, &quot;chance can also launch someone&#39;s career&quot;, and &quot;more and more today&quot;.
Like Llewyn Davis who refuses to compromise on his music, the pop star explains that in a career, &quot;the most important thing is not to get stuck in anything that can prevent us from expressing ourselves&quot;.
