What is Marine Le Pen doing with her newfound popularity with the French white working class?
She wants to use next year&#39;s European elections to create a single, anti-European anti-currency bloc in the European Parliament.
If the anti-European parties do well in these elections, which is very possible, such a bloc could control the European Parliament for the first time.
This is what I think: very soon, the anti-European and anti-single currency sentiment in Europe will unify and eventually kill the euro.
The EU will not disappear, but it will revert to something more like the free “Europe of (sovereign) Nations” favored by General de Gaulle.
Germany and some of its satellite economies could keep the euro, but France and southern Europe will regain their own currency.
I expect the UK to distance itself from this project, and hope that it will turn a blind eye to the US.
However, Washington&#39;s growing interest in the Pacific suggests that Britain will be left behind in the Atlantic.
And Scotland, in all this?
We can decide to be a region of Little England (essentially).
Or we can defend our own economic interests, which includes screwing up Berlin and Brussels.
I believe that Scotland could live with a freer European agreement provided that we keep our own motto.
Cooperation with other like-minded countries would be easier in a non-federal Europe of Nations.
Otherwise, we should imitate Norway and maintain our economic independence.
Scotland&#39;s SNP government is – and it should be noted – the most successful anti-austerity political movement in Europe, winning a spectacular majority in 2011 based on its opposition to the proposed (and implemented) deep cuts. implemented) by the Chancellor of the Labor Exchequer, Alistair Darling, and the Conservative/Liberal Democrat coalition that followed.
